## Lessons

- [Ticker Consistency]: Backend lookup should use normalized tickers, but API response keys MUST match the original requested strings to prevent frontend mapping failure.
- [Signal Priority]: When merging legacy and new structured signals (`v4_signals`), deduplication using a `Set` ensures UI cleanliness and prevents redundant tags.
- [Bulk Fetching]: Consolidating per-row metadata into a single `/api/v4/meta` call effectively eliminates network waterfalls in list-heavy views.

